
# Conventional Commits format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
#
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Formatting, missing semicolons, etc (no code change)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     Code change that improves performance
#   test:     Adding or correcting tests
#   build:    Changes to build system or dependencies
#   ci:       Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   chore:    Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#
# Scope (optional): Component name (e.g., api, ui, app, models)
#
# Subject: Brief description in imperative mood ("add feature" not "added feature")
#
# Breaking changes:
#   Add "BREAKING CHANGE:" in body/footer, or use "!" after type: feat!: ...
#
# Examples:
#   feat(ui): add filter match highlighting
#   fix(api): handle 401 errors during token refresh
#   docs: update README with new keybindings
#   chore(deps): update ratatui to 0.30
